This Week's Demos (May 11, 2026)BMaaSBare Metal Fulfillment with Profiles (
Recording
<https://drive.google.com/file/d/1DhkKFw45Ze4YBOsgjTwgPdvcY4bIiMeC/view>
15:48 - 46:25)

   -

   Introduced Ansible-driven host provisioning, replacing hardcoded logic
   with a dynamic profile parameter in the bare metal pool resource.


   -

   Profile Components: Host selectors (filtering), persistent labels
   (inventory tagging), and templates (AAP lifecycle roles).
   -

   Demonstrated Types: Agent Selection (allocates and networks hosts), Agent
   Provisioning (moves hosts to agent-managed state), and Agent
   Deprovisioning (resets hosts to bare metal).
   -

   Visibility: OpenStack inventory is now tagged with pool, host, and
   profile IDs to track OSAC resource usage.
   -

   Follow-up Actions


   -

   Expose pools and leases in the fulfillment service for admin visibility.
   -

   Extend the HostLease API for image provisioning and network attachments.
   -

   Integrate multiple backends (e.g., BCM for inventory, Metal3 for
   provisioning) using the new API.

CaaS

Catalog Items (Recording
<https://drive.google.com/file/d/1DhkKFw45Ze4YBOsgjTwgPdvcY4bIiMeC/view>
46:50 - 53:55)

   -

   Catalog items allow multiple deployment configurations to share the same
   underlying template while supporting user-defined overrides.
   -

   Demonstrated creating both a developer sandbox (one worker) and
   production cluster (three workers) from a single shared OCP 4.17 template.
   -

   Catalog items can lock specific fields (like release image) or make them
   editable with validation rules.
   -

   VM catalog items are work in progress, currently implemented for
   clusters only.
   -

   Follow-up Actions
   -

      Complete VM catalog item implementation.
      -

      Expose Catalog Items in the UI.


NVIDIA BCM (Base Command Manager) Integration (Recording
<https://drive.google.com/file/d/1l3g6nO6ZKHptqUKgU4ToLqElj-2qtTDa/view>
22:45 - 34:36)

   -

   Demonstrated importing server inventory from NVIDIA BCM into OSAC to
   support cluster provisioning.
   -

   Uses an import playbook to discover BCM nodes, create BareMetalHost
   resources, and register agents.
   -

   Labels nodes based on resource classes and periodically syncs with BCM
   to remove stale inventory.


   -

   BCM joins OpenStack and file-based inventory as a supported backend.
   -

   Follow-up actions:


   -

   Integrate with BM generic API.

EnclaveEnclave UI Configuration Wizard (Recording
<https://drive.google.com/file/d/1DhkKFw45Ze4YBOsgjTwgPdvcY4bIiMeC/view>
54:05 - 58:05)

   -

   Built a web wizard that runs in the landing zone to simplify Enclave
