      -

      Storage, including VAST
      -

      Quay mirrors
      -

      Hub cluster node management
      -

   Performs backend validation before deployment.


   -

   Includes a demo mode that replays a captured real installation at 40x
   speed.
   -

   Follow-up actions:


   -

   Integrate the Enclave UI with OSAC features beyond basic infrastructure
   setup.
   -

   Add official documentation for Enclave and the installer.

Infrastructure

Helm-Based OSAC Installer (Recording
<https://drive.google.com/file/d/1l3g6nO6ZKHptqUKgU4ToLqElj-2qtTDa/view>
3:25 - 22:22)

   -

   Demonstrated the transition from Kustomize-based installation to Helm
   charts for OSAC.
   -

   Improves production readiness by replacing a hard-to-configure,
   development-focused installer.
   -

   Uses an umbrella chart with separate charts for the OSAC operator, AAP,
   and CRDs.
   -

   Encourages production-grade management of dependencies such as Keycloak
   and Postgres instead of bundling development-oriented prerequisites.


------------------------------

Upcoming Demos:

   -

   Public IP attachment management - Extend the Public IP API so it can be
   used across OSAC services, including VMaaS, CaaS, BMaaS, and future
   consumers, instead of being limited to VM use cases.
   -

   Netris integration with OSAC Networking API - Update the existing Netris
   integration to use the standard OSAC Networking API, aligning it with the
   common networking flow.
   -

   Admin APIs - Add administrative APIs for role management, identity
   provider management, and project management.
   -

   External IDP support - API to add external IDPs.
   -

   Ansible networking VLANs network class - Add support for tenant network
   isolation using VLANs.
   -

   VM Instance Types - Provide predefined VM instance types (flavors) with
   standardized CPU, memory, and disk configurations for simplified VM
   provisioning.


